==English==
===Etymology===
From Sanskrit [[पंच]] (pa.nća) (''five'') + Persian {{FAchar|[[اب|آب]]}} (āb) (''water'') = ''The Land of Five Rivers'' + Persic adjectival form {{FAchar|[[ی]]}} (ī).
===Pronunciation===
*pän-jä'bi, {{Unicode|/pɑːnˌdʒɑːbi/}}, /<tt>pA:n"dZA:bi</tt>/

===Adjective===
'''Panjabi'''

# Of, pertaining to, descended from the people or culture of the [[Panjab]], or written in the Panjabi language

===Noun===
'''Panjabi'''

# Language spoken in Northern [[India]]

